column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Clear , No Precipitation , Calm Wind Blowing Downstream
column14: Transect 000: Discarded due to loss of GPS connection.  Note transect 001 is a much higher discharge value than the subsequect transects. Ought to have been discarded and reacquired. Averaging of all transects thought to be OK.  Measured Q is less than 50% (44.31%). StreamPro would have had difficulty with turbulence. Perhaps RiverPro will yield better results here.  BT used as reference (MBT indicates no MB). Navigation Reference: BT (BT: 70.0, GGA: 70.3, VTG: 71.2).  Right bank edges changed to square in post-processing. Left bank left as triangle.  Some QREV messages. None thought to be significant.   @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Stage data painted since ~05-26. Possible sensor movement occurs on this date (~0.05m).  First DWL at sensor line without stilling bucket. Major source of uncertainty here without use of a stilling bucket. Difficult due to depth. We cut a hole in the bottom of one and slid it up the levelling rod for subsequent DWLs.  Sensor line/block were pulled at 08:42. A block (metal) was found on the end. The line tip appeared clear. Unsure what was causing the painitng. Placed closed to vertical shoreline where line previously enetered the water.  Erroneous reset applied at 10:09. 10:10 data point ought to be deleted.  No discernible HWM.  Depth of sensor at 10:15: DWL(2.499) - Offset(1.752) = 0.747m.   ADCP by Moving Boat
GC: 0.000 HG: 2.521 Surge: 0.030  * The uncertainty value is equivalent to the surge value in eHSN.  DWL

06-16 visit records a negative cut for DWL (-0.08m) resulting in a 0.001m SRC. Negative cut in the summer? Unable to reach water surface? Previous tech confirmed this is unlikely.  Theory: Surge of 0.08 was entered as -0.08m in the ‘Distance to Water Surface’ cell of the EHSN. Additional evidence includes comment in ‘Stage Activity Summary Remarks’: TWO DWL DUE TO LARGE SURGE OF 8CM (although there was only one DWL recorded on the EHSN). This results in a DWL of 2.497m and an SRC of +0.081m which accounts for the 05-11 jump in stage trace of 0.089m (which was previously attributed to ‘ice jamming/release’. Control Condition: cic Measurement Section Co dition: b Weather Condition: 100 cc Sources:Import *Strongly suspect DWL in error by 0.3m. Total station was used. Staff gauge BM has a sticker. Suspect an incorrect number of prism rods were used. Each rod is 0.3m long. The SRC on this date was 0.281m. The next 2 subsequent field visits on March 17 and May 5 had reciprocal SRCs of -.279m and -.332m. Review of all January DWLs since 2010 show the value obtained on 2020-01-29 of 2.305m would have been the highest within the 13 year dataset.  Revising the DWL by 0.3m from 2.305m to 2.005m creates an SRC of -.019m.  The November 2019 to January 2020 trace is more realistic. The subsequent March 17 and May 5 SRC's are then more believable and the trace more realistic.  Using a DWL of 2.005m also falls within the 13 year average of January DWLs. Revised as such.-WH, May 13, 2022.
